  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3c49efe 2022-07-14T00:14:23.444892Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script script/DeploymentScript.s.sol:DeploymentScript --rpc-url $TESTNET_RPC_URL  --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHey folks! So our team is running a hardhat node on an EC2 instance that is a fork of mainnet to do out testing. I am unable to run the foundry script with the command above when passing in the RPC url of our test node. I get the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nProviderError(SerdeJson { err: Error(\"invalid type: null, expected u64\", line: 1, column: 26), text: \"{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"id\\\":null,\\\"error\\\":{\\\"code\\\":-32600,\\\"message\\\":\\\"Invalid request\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"message\\\":\\\"Invalid request\\\"}}}\" })\r\n```\r\n\r\nOur node is running correctly and accepting txns from our brownie project as we would expect. My suspicion is the rpc call foundry is generating isn't playing nice with the hardhat node. \r\n\r\nI also tried the command with the --hh flag to see if it helped but no luck on that front also. ",
